The role of the Dealing Room Risk Manager is to ensure the effectivness of Market Risk frameworks by providing oversight and analysis of traded and non-traded market risk activity as well as facilitating communication and collaboration between teams in Singapore, Mumbai, Fiji and PNG offices. In this role, you will support the development and maintenance of robust and sustainable market risk management frameworks as it applies to activity in Asia and provide consultancy on market risk-related issues and engage with the business to improve risk management capability and new product development.

Key Accountabilities
 To participate in the development of risk measuring and monitoring techniques and tools
 Monitor and analyse traded and/or non-traded market risk activities and performance including oversight of limit management within delegated authorities
 To support Market Risk in its implementation of a new Market Risk engine
 To support Market Risk in Westpac뭩 IBOR transition programme
 Engage with the business to improve risk management capabilities, facilitating the introduction of new products and contributing on relevant market risk-related matters
 Facilitate market risk management related aspects of business changes and initiatives
 Provide timely response to ad hoc investigations, analysis and delegated tasks
 Delivers tasks delegated by Head of Market &amp; Liquidity Risk, Asia Pacific
 Provide communication to regional mangement and committees on market risk related matters
 Establish and maintain local policies and protocols in support of the global market risk management framework
 Contribute internal, external and prudential reporting, including production of local/regional market risk reports as required
 Maintain up-to-date knowledge and adherance to prudential requirements of local regulators
 Communicate with other areas of the bank that supply data
 Provide general education training and/or workshops for regional offices on market risk related topics as required

Knowledge and Experience
 2-5 years experience in risk management in a financial markets environment
 Bachelors degree or equivalent qualification in relevant discipline
 Relevant regulatory knowledge and specific subject matter expertise in traded and/or non-traded market risk management
 Demonstrated ability in market risk oversight and governance in a range of asset classes and risk types
 Practical experience in dealing with operational process and procedure in financial markets environment
 Good written and verbal communication skills and negotiating skills
 Business knowledge
 Good Excel, VBA, SQL skills
 Teamwork and collaboration
 Consulting and advisory
 Strong problem solving ability with attention to detail